gw.pl.logging

Class LoggerImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.pl.logging.LoggerImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILogger, org.slf4j.Logger
    Deprecated. 
    keep using in Emerald and replace with org.slf4j.Logger in F.

    @Deprecated
public class LoggerImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements Logger
    Should be removed and replaced by the plain slf4j Logger class. Forwards all methods to SLF4J logger. Is kept here for backwards compatibility with Diamond logging.

      • warn

        @Deprecated
public void warn(java.lang.Object object)
        Deprecated. use the slf4j method
        WARN is used to indicate that the system has taken a default course of action that will result in something unexpected for the user. For example, too many unsucessful logins will result in a user being locked out of the system, or an assignment cannot be found for a claim which results in a default assignment being made. These are both legal but possibly surprising to an end user.
        Specified by:
        warn in interface ILogger
